## Task Completion:

## 1. Analyze and Describe the Main Target Image:
- **Count & Layers:**
    - The structure is composed of **13 blocks**.
    - It has **3 layers** in the main body and an additional separate section with **2 layers**.

- **Spatial Relationships:**
    - **Layer 1 (Bottom Layer of Main Body):**
        - Three red arch blocks are placed side-by-side forming a base.
        - Two orange wedge blocks are positioned at the front ends of the arch blocks, acting as ramps or supports.
    - **Layer 2 (Middle Layer of Main Body):**
        - A yellow semi-circle block is placed on top of the leftmost arch block.
        - A green rectangular block (horizontal orientation) is placed on top of the middle arch block.
        - A yellow rectangular block (horizontal orientation) is placed on top of the rightmost arch block.
        - A smaller orange rectangular block is placed on the rightmost arch block, next to the yellow rectangular block.
    - **Layer 3 (Top Layer of Main Body):**
        - A blue cube is placed on top of the yellow semi-circle block.
        - An orange house-shaped block is placed on top of the green rectangular block.
        - A yellow rectangular block (vertical orientation) is placed on top of the yellow rectangular block from layer 2.
        - Another orange house-shaped block is placed on top of the smaller orange rectangular block from layer 2.
    - **Separate Section (Right Side):**
        - **Layer 1:** A red rectangular block with a circular hole (vertical orientation) is placed on the ground.
        - **Layer 2:** A green rectangular block (horizontal orientation) is placed inside the circular hole of the red block.
